{"tid":2216145,"cid":5,"subCid":11,"title":"路透社訪問黃偉然太太 : 願以餘生守候丈夫","createTime":"2020-09-24T12:51:09.000Z","updateTime":"2020-09-24T16:14:34.000Z","uid":240362,"like":26,"dislike":1,"uniUserReply":13,"replies":[{"pid":"90bdc59cd54c37b62cbf872ba9aed7fa68b9813b","tid":2216145,"uid":240362,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-09-24T12:51:09.000Z","msg":"<a href=\"https://www.reuters.com/article/hongkong-security-detainees/feature-a-hong-kong-protesters-farewell-note-and-failed-escape-idUSL5N2GH08Y\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Farticle%2Fhongkong-security-detainees%2Ffeature-a-hong-kong-protesters-farewell-note-and-failed-escape-idUSL5N2GH08Y&d=6i5jd82mnfhmr%2B7rEyOheFmNgp3wQ%2BT5fJEe%2BG4C8OY%3D&h=9d4ddb0e\" data-ef-url=\"https://embed.lih.kg/frame?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Farticle%2Fhongkong-security-detainees%2Ffeature-a-hong-kong-protesters-farewell-note-and-failed-escape-idUSL5N2GH08Y&h=638a97bc\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://www.reuters.com/article/hongkong-security-detainees/feature-a-hong-kong-protesters-farewell-note-and-failed-escape-idUSL5N2GH08Y</a><br />\n<br />\n<strong><span class=\"red\">&quot;&ldquo;He doesn&rsquo;t need to worry about us. I will safeguard this family with his mother,&rdquo; Wong&rsquo;s wife told Reuters. &ldquo;I will wait for him for the rest of my life.&rdquo;</span></strong><br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;I am sorry and thanks for accompanying me throughout the years,&rdquo; the hand-written note found on a desk at their home read. &ldquo;I&rsquo;m sorry that I can&rsquo;t walk with you anymore... Please take care of yourselves.&rdquo;<br />\n<br />\nWong, 30, an unemployed dock mechanic facing criminal charges relating to his participation in the protests that roiled Hong Kong last year, had scribbled his message to his wife and his mother on a page torn from a notebook.<br />\n<br />\nHe apologised for not repairing their ramshackle house before he departed. &ldquo;I still haven&rsquo;t had the time to fix the rooftop of our home, but I&rsquo;m afraid I won&rsquo;t have such a chance anymore,&rdquo; he wrote.<br />\n<br />\nWong&rsquo;s wife and mother set out on a desperate search to find him, worried he had killed himself, they told Reuters.<br />\n<br />\nTen of the 12 arrested after the failed attempt to flee by speedboat to Taiwan had faced charges including rioting, arson and police assault. One stood accused of colluding with foreign forces under the new law.<br />\n<br />\nWong had been arrested on Jan. 16 for allegedly making explosive substances. He was only one of hundreds of Hong Kong democracy activists and protesters who have left the city by sea and air over the past year or so.<br />\n<br />\nHe joined a group of 10 other men and one woman before dawn on Aug. 23 to board a speedboat berthed in a quiet fishing village before setting off for Taiwan, around 600 km (375 miles) away. If weather conditions are good, the trip can be completed in less than a day.<br />\n<br />\nWong met his wife, originally from mainland China, during a holiday in Vietnam in 2014. They moved into a modest village house in Hong Kong looking onto fields. But they were happy, she said.<br />\n<br />\nBefore Wong&rsquo;s arrest in January, their life was simple, she said. They dreamt of finally going on a honeymoon in Japan, reshooting their wedding photos and having a child after saving up enough. They planned to buy a flat and retire in mainland China.<br />\n<br />\nHe was released on bail on Feb. 14. The High Court ordered surveillance cameras to be installed at Wong&rsquo;s home. A date had not been set for his trial.<br />\n<br />\nAfter Wong&rsquo;s arrest, his mother said they stopped meeting relatives and friends, worrying they would cause them trouble by association.<br />\n<br />\nWhen Wong fled and skipped bail, $96,000 was confiscated by the court together with fees his wife said she had set aside to hire an independent lawyer. Half of the family&rsquo;s savings vanished, his wife added.<br />\n<br />\nWong&rsquo;s wife said the mainland lawyer she hired to represent her husband was not allowed to meet him. That lawyer declined to comment to Reuters, saying authorities warned him his lawyer&rsquo;s licence would be revoked if he conducted media interviews.<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;He doesn&rsquo;t need to worry about us. I will safeguard this family with his mother,&rdquo; Wong&rsquo;s wife told Reuters. &ldquo;I will wait for him for the rest of my life.&rdquo;"},{"pid":"da65803373faf4eebcfe90a3b36402014657535b","tid":2216145,"uid":103965,"like":3,"dislike":0,"score":3,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-09-24T12:53:12.000Z","msg":"當 你從沒怨 能捱這麼久<img src=\"/assets/faces/fs/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"c67357d023422acc0433f53254fccda5da43a4cb","tid":2216145,"uid":240362,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"da65803373faf4eebcfe90a3b36402014657535b","tid":2216145,"uid":103965,"like":3,"dislike":0,"score":3,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-09-24T12:53:12.000Z","msg":"當 你從沒怨 能捱這麼久<img src=\"/assets/faces/fs/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-09-24T12:53:40.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/notcry.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/notcry.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/notcry.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/notcry.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"0cc6e1eafbb18bd8db06750c55a7f3695749e3f8","tid":2216145,"uid":240362,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-09-24T12:55:39.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/drum.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/drum.gif\" class=\"hk